# React Component Rules

## Styling

- **Tailwind CSS only** - No CSS modules, styled-components, or inline styles
- **PDM Theme classes**: `pdm-bg`, `pdm-fg`, `pdm-accent`, `pdm-border`
- **Status colors**: `pdm-success`, `pdm-warning`, `pdm-error`, `pdm-info`
- **Sidebar text must be left-aligned** - Use `text-left` class in ActivityBar.tsx

## Component Patterns

- Functional components with hooks only (no class components)
- One component per file, co-locate related components
- Default exports for components, named exports for utilities
- TypeScript with explicit prop types

## State Management

- `useState` for local UI state
- `usePDMStore` (Zustand) for global state
- Never mutate Zustand state directly - use `set` function
- Use selectors to avoid unnecessary re-renders

## Hooks Rules

- Hooks at top level only
- Custom hooks must start with `use`
- `useEffect`: Always include cleanup, include all dependencies
- `useMemo`/`useCallback`: Only for expensive computations

## Import Order

1. External packages (react, etc.)
2. Internal modules (@/lib, @/stores)
3. Relative imports (./Component)
